	CSS declarations (property and value)
- font-family - define the typeface of an element
- font-size - define the size of text displayed
- font-weight - define how thin or thick text is displayed
- text-align - define the places text in the left, right or center
- color - define the color of the text
- background-color - define the colo behind the text
- opacity - make an element transparent
- background-image - set the background of an element to an image
- width and height - specifies the width and height of the content area
- padding - specifies the amount of space between the content area and the border (top, bottom, right, left)
- border - specifies the trickness and style of the border surrounding the content area and padding
	width (thin, medium, thick)
	style (none, dotted, solid)
	color
- border-radius - modify the corners of an element's border box
- margin - specifies the amount of space between the border and the outsite edge of the element (top, bottom, right, left)
	top and bottom - not sum of their adjacent margins
	left and right - sum of their adjacent margins
- min-width - ensures a minimum width of an element's box
- max-width - ensures a maximum width of an element's box
- min-height - ensures a minimum height for an element's box
- max-height - ensures a maximum height for an element's box
- overflow - control what happens to content that spills, or overflows, outside its box (hidden, scroll, visible)
- visibility - set to one of the following values: hidden or visible
- display - remove (none) or add (block) completely an element from the web page
